Presenting a behind the scenes look of our new cookie jar photo, along with some tips and tricks to help you capture some epic shots of your own pet! 🍪 I edited this photo with the help of @lightroom which I’ve been using for editing since the beginning! We started with a subtle preset and adjusted its intensity with the new slider tool. The healing tool allowed me to remove crumbs, reflections on his nose, and fill in blank spaces between the cookies. The masking tool allows me to select and edit specific parts of the photo, such as adding texture to the cookies and brightening shadows. The best part about #lightroom is our photos are stored to the cloud, to ensure I never lose these precious memories of Bear.

Wishing you all mouthfuls of yummy snacks in 2023! 🍪 Our friends @stellaandchewys sent us a holiday cookie kit which was a huge hit with Bear! We wanted to share this easy recipe for your pups to enjoy this holiday season: 🥳
 
Ingredients:
2 cups whole wheat flour
1 large egg lightly beaten
3 TBSP rolled oats
2/3 cups #stellaandchewys bountiful bone broth
Top with plain yogurt or peanut butter and sprinkle with Stella & Chewy’s Marie’s Magical Dinner Dust 

How to Bake:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F 
2. Gently whisk bone broth and egg together, slowly mix in whole wheat flour and oats
3. Roll out on lightly floured surface to approx. 1/4 inch thickness, cut out cookies with cookie cutters and transfer to parchment lined cookie sheet
4. Bake for 10 min.
5. Top with plain yogurt or peanut butter and sprinkle with dinner dust ✨
and now I bet it’s one of the best views you saw too. 😉 Enjoy this gorgeous view all year long with our 2023 calendar. ✨

Head to the store locator tool at https://www.stellaandchewys.com/where-to-buy/ to find a neighborhood pet store in your area and surprise your pup with their own yummy snacks 👅

It has been a rainy week here so we made a tasty “hot cocoa” alternative for dogs. All you need is:

-2 cups coconut milk or water
-2 TBSP CAROB powder (not cocoa, which is toxic to dogs)
Combine milk/water and Carob powder over medium heat.

Optional toppings:
- @stellaandchewys carnivore crunch as a yummy marshmallow alternative
-a pinch of cinnamon
-honey drizzle

Allow the drink to COOL before serving to your dog. Get cozy together and enjoy a small serving! (Recipe makes 2-3 servings)

Up among the stars is a dog I’ll never forget. 🌟 This month marked 17 years since I first picked up a camera and made this boy my muse. We both were just kiddos back then and instagram didn’t exist. Thank you for leaving me with the lifetime gift of photography, Champ. 🌟

What do you do on rainy days with your dog? ☔️ It has been the rainiest season ever here in California, so I’ve had to get creative with making Bear’s meals mentally stimulating. Instead of gobbling his meal down in 15 seconds flat, it takes him about 15 minutes to finish a frozen stuffed Toppl. We used:
🦆 1 @stellandchewys raw duck patty
(if you feed dry food, soak the kibble in hot water to soften.)
🍦1 plain yogurt & berry pupsicle 
🧊 1 #stellaandchewys bone broth pupsicle 
(To make the pupsicles, just freeze the ingredients in an ice cube tray.)
🍓strawberries & blueberries
🥦broccoli & carrot 

When you’re done stuffing the Toppl, put it in the freezer to extend meal time.

Ice cream sandwiches for dogs 🍦 

Don’t let excess fruit go to waste - we had some extra bananas that were going to go bad soon, so we froze them and made some dog-friendly ice cream!

Blend together:
-1 frozen banana 🍌 
-1/2 cup coconut milk 🥥
-1/2 cup plain yogurt 🍦 
-(optional) 1 heaping spoonful of peanut butter 🥜 

Freeze for 4 hours, let it thaw for a softer consistency. Put one scoop of ice cream between two @stellaandchewys dinner patties and serve! 🤤 

♻️ P.S. did you know the #stellaandchewys freeze-dried raw packaging can be recycled at local stores that collect plastic bags?
Happy 7th birthday to Bear! 🎂He enjoyed his yearly peanut butter dog cake. 👅 Can you believe it? Who has been following this boy since he was just a pup? 🥺

Thank you all for the warm birthday wishes! We never know how many birthdays we get to spend with them, so each one counts. Celebrate your dog every day because it goes by in the blink of an eye! Every year, he gets his favorite peanut butter cake and I take tons of photos. 🥳 How do you celebrate your dog’s birthday/gotcha day?

Thanks again all for the birthday wishes for Bear last month! 🎂 We had lots of questions on dog-friendly cake recipes, so here’s a delicious one for pupcakes (or cake if you prefer):

🥕 1/2 cup shredded carrots
🥚 1 egg
🥥 1 TB coconut oil
🍜 3 oz @stellaandchewys bountiful bone broth
🥜 2 TB PB
Mix the above ingredients in a bowl. Then mix in:
🌾 2/3 cup wheat flour
🥄 1 tsp baking soda
(Makes 4 pupcakes)
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20-25 minutes. Test by poking with a fork, it’s ready when the fork comes out dry. 

Frosting: 
1/2 cup plain yogurt + 1/2 cup peanut butter, mix. Then:
✨Sprinkle with #stellaandchewys Marie’s Magic Dinner Dust✨
Enjoy!! 👅

Invite your best furry friends over this summer and serve these dog-friendly donuts! Bear loved it a hole lot. 🍩
🎃 1/2 cup plain pumpkin
🥜 1/4 cup peanut butter
🥥 2 tbsp coconut oil 
🥚 1 egg
🍯 1 tbsp honey 
Mix wet ingredients together
Then mix in:
🌾 1 cup wheat flour
🥄 1/2 tsp baking soda
(Makes about 4-6 depending on size. Feed treats in moderation & share the rest with friends! Bear got 1/2 a donut.)
Place into an oiled Donut-shaped baking tray and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Let them cool before adding “frosting.”

☁️ Frosting:
-Plain yogurt for white “frosting” 
-For pink “frosting” blend a handful of strawberries and then mix into plain yogurt.
-if the yogurt is too runny you can place the donut in the freezer for 10 minutes and it’ll harden slightly
-(optional) peanut butter and honey drizzle 

🥓 Then top with your favorite treats! We used:
-@stellaandchewys Crav’n Bac’n Bites and chopped Just Jerky Bites
-#stellaandchewys Marie’s Magical Dinner Dust ✨

Bear is here to send everyone who has lost a pet lots of love today for #RainbowBridgeRememberanceDay 🌈 Not only am I keeping pets at the rainbow bridge in my thoughts today (such as our own Angel Champ), I’m grateful for blessings like Bear, as they are truly the rainbow to look forward to following the grief. ⛈️ Tell us the name(s) of your rainbow bridge pets. 🌈 Today I am remembering Angel Champ who was my original photography muse, as well as Angel Rocky my childhood Golden Retriever who is the reason I fell in love with the breed. 🧡💛 Also can’t forget Angel Pugsly who was the biggest fighter I’ve ever known and was like a brother to Champ and Bear.

🎃 Pumpkin Pie for Dogs 🥧 

Happy October! Pumpkin is one of Bear’s favorite foods, so of course I had to make him a dog-friendly pumpkin pie for fall. It definitely was a challenge getting a shot of the pie intact, because he couldn’t wait to take a bite. 😂 

For the crust:
🌾 1 cup whole wheat flour
🎃 1/2 cup plain pumpkin 
🍜 3 tbsp @stellaandchewys bountiful bone broth - to add superfoods and tasty fall flavors like cinammon. 🍂 
Mix above ingredients together in a bowl until it forms into dough, knead into a ball, roll it out until flat, and place it into a pie tin. Bake at 350 degrees for 8 minutes. 

For the filling:
🎃 1 cup plain pumpkin purée 
🍌 1 mashed banana 
🍦 1 tbsp plain yogurt 
🥚 1 egg
Mix above ingredients together and pour over the crust. Bake again at 425 degrees for 15 minutes, then continue baking at 350 degrees until the center filling is set. 

☁️ Top with whipped cream and a pinch of #stellaandchewys Marie’s Magical Dinner Dust! ✨ 

Let it cool and enjoy! 🐶 (filling will firm up more as you let it cool, refrigerating helps too!)

Do you include your pet in your holiday cards? 🎄 If so, you’ll want to use these tips and @adobeexpress templates to create your custom card when you’re done!
1. 📷 Cameras can be scary for some dogs. Start slow and build a positive association with treats; first for simply sniffing the camera, and then each time the shutter and/or flash goes off.
2. 🐶 Motivate your dog to look at the camera! Think about what gets your dog’s attention: is it treats, toys, or the sound of a squeaker?
3. 💡 Lighting is key! When indoors, you’ll want to shoot facing a window for the best natural light. Use a softbox or ring light if your home doesn’t get much natural light. For outdoors, avoid the midday sun as it creates harsh shadows. Early morning, golden hour, or the shade is best.
4. 🎄 Share your photos! Create custom cards, invitations, posters, social media posts and more with Adobe Express. #AdobePartner

🥛 2 cups coconut milk or water
🤎2 TBSP CAROB powder (never use cocoa)
🐶Instead of marshmallows, top with @stellaandchewys carnivore crunch or meal mixers. 
Stir milk/water and Carob powder together over medium heat. Wait for it to cool before serving. 

Happy Holidays! 🎄Enjoy this cozy drink this holiday season! ☕️
